It is now getting to a critical point that 80 per cent of the population is under 35 years.Our democracy has made gains over the years, which justifies inclusion of critical constituencies — among them the youth — in any political discourse and debate. As Kenyans celebrate Jamhuri Day, it should offer a reflective moment on the foundation of our nation, which was premised on the wrong footing as far as the welfare of the youth is concerned- both in leadership and economic prosperity.
Although the state was crafted by a cabal of young people, a mechanism of creating room for the next generation has been lacking, leading to accumulation of resources and domination of power among a few people- leading to the huge wealth inequality we are facing today as a nation.



