It is now getting to a critical point that 80 per cent of the population is under 35 years. There is an undeniable fact here that youth voice and action must be considered as essential in bringing about change and lasting solutions in the country’s crises.
Turmoil and instability
The struggle for independence, multiparty and the 2010 Constitution are some of the positive heritage of Kenya’s old generation. Our democracy has made gains over the years, which justifies inclusion of critical constituencies — among them the youth — in any political discourse and debate.



