The challenges facing the country, critical being the division between haves and have-nots, call for bold approaches to building a better country.
This divide is likely to create a country characterised by more turmoil and instability. No one can rest comfortably in a country where the rich cannot sleep because the poor are awake and hungry, as African saying goes.
It is the responsibility of the country and its youth to take bold steps required to make Kenya more inclusive, free of corruption, ethnicity among other vices that continue to inhibit progress.
This can only be achieved if economic and social development programmes are deliberately planned to incorporate youth agenda. Presently, due to their worsening plight, many young people feel betrayed by the country they love.



